### Step 5 — Weekly brief summary

After processing all URLs for today, write/append to 
`~/Seo-workflow-mindtalk/mindtalk-setup/logs/briefs-[WEEK-START-DATE].txt`:
- List of all briefs created this week with URLs and keywords
- Running count toward the 20/week limit

## Important rules

- Write briefs in clear, actionable language — a non-SEO content writer must understand them
- Do NOT write the actual content — only the brief and direction
- Do NOT edit any MDX files during this task
- If a competitor page blocks browser access, note it and use the next competitor
- If no DIRECT_COMPETITORs rank above us (only HIGH_DA/aggregators), still write the 
  brief — use PAA questions and our own thin sections as the gap analysis source
- Clinical accuracy matters: do not suggest adding medical claims without a source
- All suggested content must align with Mindtalk's mental health and psychiatry focus

## Step 6 — Post to Slack

Post a summary to **#seo-workflow-mindtalk** (channel ID: `C0AUAPS4J83`) using `slack_send_message`.

Format:

```
📝 *Content Briefs — [TODAY'S DATE]*
Site: mindtalk.in

Briefs created today: [N]
Weekly total: [N]/20

[For each brief:]
> 📄 *[Primary Keyword]* — [severity]
> URL: [url_path]
